data.meta_description:
20K likes, 145 comments - billboard on April 18, 2024: "A new documentary titled ‘Call Me Country: Beyoncé & Nashville’s Renaissance’ is slated to hit Max.⁠
⁠
The upcoming documentary will provide a look at the impact of acts like Beyoncé and Lil Nas X on the contemporary country music scene and how their contributions connect to the history of Black artists in Nashville. It will also feature interviews with Brothers Osborne, “Texas Hold ‘Em” banjo player Rhiannon Giddens and more.⁠
⁠
Details are at the link in bio.".
